1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the ergodic secrecy rate of an artificial noise scheme in MIMO systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a physical layer security approach using artificial noise to improve the secrecy rate of MIMO systems, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of artificial noise in MIMO systems, which is a topic relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system-level approach to improve the security of MIMO systems using artificial noise, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although less likely, the paper may also fall under the category of multimedia as it deals with the transmission of signals in MIMO systems.
